Put your trust in the sky, but put more in Honorius· Beneath his auspices I, his soldier, range the bound- less seas nor look to the Plough or the Bear to guide me. Make no account of BooteS, sailor; launch your bark in mid tempest. If winds and storms deny me Libya, my emperor’s fortune will grant it.”

The fleet is launched. They pass Liguria on their left hand, Etruria on their right, avoiding the sunken reefs of Corsica.
